# devops-exp-3
devops-exp-3
CI Pipeline Lab: Python App → GitHub Actions → Docker Hub
✅ Step 1 — Create GitHub repo

Open GitHub → New repository → name it python-ci-docker-lab

✅ Step 2 — Open Command Prompt

Press Win + R → type cmd → Enter

✅ Step 3 — Create project folder
mkdir python-ci-docker-lab
cd python-ci-docker-lab
mkdir tests
mkdir .github
mkdir .github\workflows
✅ Step 4 — Create app.py
notepad app.py

Paste:

def add(a, b):
    return a + b

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("Hello from Python CI Lab!")
    print("2 + 3 =", add(2, 3))

Save and close.

✅ Step 5 — Create tests\test_app.py
notepad tests\test_app.py

Paste:

from app import add

def test_add():
    assert add(2, 3) == 5
    assert add(-1, 1) == 0

Save and close.

✅ Step 6 — Create requirements.txt
notepad requirements.txt

Paste:

pytest==8.3.2

Save and close.

✅ Step 7 — Create Dockerfile
notepad Dockerfile

Paste:

FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

Save as:

File name: Dockerfile
Save as type: All Files
✅ Step 8 — Create workflow file
notepad .github\workflows\ci-dockerhub.yml

Paste:

name: ci-dockerhub

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]

jobs:
  build-test-push:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Set up Python
        uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: '3.11'

      - name: Install deps
        run: |
          python -m pip install --upgrade pip
          pip install -r requirements.txt

      - name: Run tests
        run: pytest -q

      - name: Login to Docker Hub
        uses: docker/login-action@v3
        with:
          username: ${{ secrets.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME }}
          password: ${{ secrets.DOCKERHUB_TOKEN }}

      - name: Build and push
        uses: docker/build-push-action@v6
        with:
          context: .
          push: true
          tags: ${{ secrets.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME }}/python-ci-lab:latest

Save and close.

✅ Step 9 — Push to GitHub
git init
git add .
git commit -m "init lab"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/santhosh444-ai/python-ci-docker-lab.git
git push -u origin main
✅ Step 10 — Add GitHub secrets

Open GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions

Add:

DOCKERHUB_USERNAME = your Docker Hub username
DOCKERHUB_TOKEN = your Docker Hub access token

✅ Step 11 — Check workflow

Open GitHub repo → Actions tab

You should see:

tests running
docker image building
image pushing
✅ Step 12 — Check Docker Hub

Open Docker Hub and see:

python-ci-lab

✅ What is not needed

You can skip:

local docker test
local python run
.gitignore
tag release
qemu/buildx/manual extras
✅ What to tell staff

“I created a Python app, added a test file, created a GitHub Actions workflow, stored Docker Hub username and token in GitHub Secrets, then pushed code to GitHub. The workflow automatically ran tests, built the Docker image, and pushed it to Docker Hub.”
